{"questionId":"4150869","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The student collects the following data.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table style=\"height:248px;border-color:#000000;width:443.55px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"o\" cellpadding=\"2\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Gauge pressure Δ<em>p</em> / kPa</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Maximum force <em>F</em><sub>max</sub> / N</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">10</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">108</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">20</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">133</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">30</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">158</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">40</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">170</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">50</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">188</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">60</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">192</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">70</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">206</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:208px;text-align:center;\">80</td>\n<td style=\"width:216.55px;text-align:center;\">220</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The student initially hypothesizes that <em>F</em><sub>max</sub> is proportional to Δ<em>p</em>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Draw&nbsp;the absolute uncertainty determined in part (d)(i) as an error bar on the graph.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>error bar drawn at 30 kPa from 34 × 10<sup>5</sup> to 46 × 10<sup>5</sup> N<sup>3</sup> ✓</p>\n<p><em><br>Allow ± half square on each side of the bar or one square overall (± 2 × 10<sup>5</sup>)</em></p>\n<p><